race.comment: WATERMELON (1) goes well for hoop Youngberry who has two wins and a placing from just four steers and again gets the benefit of her 3kg claim. Is a three-time winner over this track and trip and should be going very close again with any luck from the draw. NEOCLASSICISM (4) saves his best form for this poly surface with two wins and ten placings from just 16 attempts. Rates a genuine top-three prospect against this line-up. FRIEND IN NEED (2) has been right there in all four runs this campaign and looks to be building up to another victory. In the mix. TARADALE (6) has gotten better with each run this time in and will be at peak fitness now fourth-up. Capable of a bold showing. VISCOUNT SYDNEY (10) is a last-start winner who may run a race at odds.
